"from\": 4885, \"to\": 5025, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ms Coventry, who is herself a former Olympic swimmer from Zimbabwe, was elected to the position earlier this year.\", \"from\": 5029, \"to\": 5143, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5032, \"end\": 5040, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coventry\", \"score\": 0.9999228657375601, \"rank\": 7.394143815146004e-05, \"text\": \"Coventry\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coventry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coventry\"}, {\"begin\": 5087, \"end\": 5095, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zimbabwe\", \"score\": 0.9999959776215699, \"rank\": 3.7876818941031965e-06, \"text\": \"Zimbabwe\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zimbabwe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zimbabwe\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Speaking on her current rules in July: \\\"We understand there will be differences depending on the sports.\", \"from\": 5145, \"to\": 5249, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We should make the effort to place emphasis on the protection of the female category and we should ensure that this is done in consensus with all the stakeholders.\", \"from\": 5251, \"to\": 5415, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But we need to do that with a scientific approach and the inclusion of the international federations who have already done a lot of work in this area.\\\"\", \"from\": 5417, \"to\": 5569, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The new policy will also reportedly cover differences in sex development athletes.\", \"from\": 5571, \"to\": 5653, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This would affect those who were raised as girls from birth but have male chromosomes and male levels of testosterone.\", \"from\": 5655, \"to\": 5773, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The new rules, which will aim to make the games fairer for all participants, follow a trans row at the boxing tournament at the Paris 2024 Olympics, where Imane Khelif from Algeria and Taiwan's Lin Yu-Ting, won gold medals despite having been disqualified from the previous year's World Championships for allegedly failing to meet gender eligibility criteria.\", \"from\": 5775, \"to\": 6134, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5930, \"end\": 5942, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"score\": 0.9999996421623295, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Imane Khelif\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\"}, {\"begin\": 5948, \"end\": 5955, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"score\": 0.9999999271667575, \"rank\": 4.947169322931457e-08, \"text\": \"Algeria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\"}, {\"begin\": 5960, \"end\": 5966, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"score\": 0.9998643501070665, \"rank\": 0.00013310356872116207, \"text\": \"Taiwan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\"}, {\"begin\": 5969, \"end\": 5980, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lin Yu-Ting\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"World Boxing, the new international boxing federation, which the IOC has recognised since Paris, has now introduced mandatory sex testing and has said Khelif will not be able to compete in the female category until she undergoes the test.\", \"from\": 6136, \"to\": 6374, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6201, \"end\": 6204, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.755923737446058e-29, \"text\": \"IO